    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <dateline>June 6<hi rend="superscript">th.</hi> 1773.</dateline>

                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have sent <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName>
                    an answer &amp; a <rs type="art" ref="ar0116">set of his prints</rs> that he may
                    shew his friends that something is going on for him. I wish <persName ref="pe0192">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Elliot</persName> would fix on
                    his own Bookseller <persName ref="pe0043">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Cadel</persName> who is able &amp; eminent in his profession. as to the
                    prints I Imagine they will not cost so much as I said perhaps they may come
                    under 50.<hi rend="superscript">L</hi> as many will be guinea or two guinea
                    plates only.</p>
                <p>I only wish for the finishing of two to send a set as you direct: perhaps 2 sets
                    that you put them in different hands. I think some friend should recomend
                        <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName> for the
                    patronage of <persName ref="pe0132">Sir L. Dundas</persName>. He wishes to
                    dedicate the work to me. but I think <persName ref="pe0132">Sir L.</persName>
                    the properer person &amp; one who may serve him better. excuse a short Letter
                    for the weather is most intolerably hot.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am Dear Sir <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> faithful humble
                            Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Tho.
                    Pennant</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>

                <postscript>
                    <p>Has <persName ref="pe0104">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Gough</persName>
                        read <bibl type="authorial">
                            <title ref="bi0058">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Lows M.S.</title>
                        </bibl>
                    </p>
                </postscript>

            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
